Module com.example.teach
Package com.example.teach.model

Class Homework

java.lang.Object
com.example.teach.model.Homework
public class Homework extends Object
Represents a homework assignment associated with a subject and week.

This class encapsulates the homework's metadata including title, description, due dates, and visibility windows (release and open dates).

      public Homework(String subjectId, String week, String title, String description, String dueDate, String releaseDate, String openDate, String id)
      Constructs a new Homework object.
      Parameters:
      subjectId - ID of the subject
      week - The academic week (e.g., "Week 1")
      title - Title of the homework
      description - Description or content of the homework
      dueDate - The due date for submission
      releaseDate - When the homework is released (optional)
      openDate - When submissions can begin (optional)
      id - Unique ID (can be generated with UUID)
